# OpenClaw Automation Best Practices Report
**Research Date:** March 5, 2026
**Sources:** Yu Wenhao Tools Guide, Towards AI, Stormap, Markaicode, Official Docs

## Executive Summary

After researching OpenClaw automation best practices from multiple expert sources, I've identified **key misconfigurations** in our current setup that prevent true autonomous operation.

### The Core Problem

Our current setup uses **heartbeat polling** (I wake up every X minutes, check HEARTBEAT.md, then go back to sleep). This is **reactive**, not truly **continuous**.

For true "work continuously while you sleep" autonomy, we need **cron jobs** with **isolated sessions** or **mode: session** with **thread: true**.

---

## What We Got Wrong Yesterday

### Current Setup (Heartbeat Polling) ❌
```
Heartbeat fires → I check DAILY_TASKS.md → Report status → Sleep
```
**Problem:** I only work when heartbeat wakes me. If you don't message me, I don't work.

### What We Actually Need ✅

**Option 1: Cron Jobs (True Autonomy)**
```bash
openclaw cron add \
  --name "Continuous Work" \
  --every 300000 \
  --session isolated \
  --message "Read DAILY_TASKS.md, execute next task if any, then check capability_changelog.md for improvements"
```
**Result:** I work autonomously every 5 minutes, even when you're not chatting.

**Option 2: Mode: Session (Thread-Bound Persistent Agent)**
```
sessions_spawn with runtime="acp", mode="session", thread=true
```
**Result:** A persistent session that stays alive, continuously processing.

